Essential Properties

Core elements needed for a thing to be what it is.

Accidental Properties

Traits that could be taken away from an object without making it a different thing.

Accidental properties are easy to pick out.  Essential properties can be quite difficult to identify the more it changes.

Existentialists deny the very existence of essential properties.
